Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} into thirds, cutting any thick stems lengthways.

Peel and grate your @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, stir in the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Pour the @boiled water{220%ml} for the bulgur into the saucepan.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Pop a #lid{} on the saucepan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}, pepper chunks and the @chermoula spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir to combine.

Fry until the pepper has softened and the chicken is golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir occasionally and lower the heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken is cooked, add the Tenderstem® broccoli to the frying pan and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}, then add a splash of @water{}.

Pop a lid on the frying pan, or cover in some #foil{}. Cook until tender, a further ~{2-3%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the bulgur is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{}.

Stir through the @harissa paste{50%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder).

Add the harissa bulgur to the chicken and veg pan, then gently mix together until combined. Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Spoon the chicken and veg bulgur into your #bowls{}.

Finish with a dollop of @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}. Enjoy!